      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add OpenSandbox provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds an `opensandbox` delegated-run provider backed by the OpenSandbox Go SDK. The provider supports sandbox lifecycle, archive-based workspace sync, command execution through execd, local lease claims scoped to a trusted API endpoint, list/status/stop/doctor flows, provider flags, config/env wiring, documentation, and a live smoke script.\n\nRefs #266\n\n## Notable behavior\n\n- Requires `CRABBOX_OPENSANDBOX_API_KEY` or `OPEN_SANDBOX_API_KEY` at runtime.\n- Requires an explicit trusted API URL from `--opensandbox-api-url`, `CRABBOX_OPENSANDBOX_API_URL`, or `OPEN_SANDBOX_API_URL`; repository YAML cannot redirect a shell-provided API key.\n- Allows plain HTTP only for localhost/loopback development endpoints.\n- Stores local lease claims as `osbx_<sandbox-id>` and verifies matching remote ownership metadata before reuse or deletion.\n- Runs delegated commands through execd with forwarded environment values in the request body rather than argv.\n- Uses a keepalive entrypoint for created sandboxes, resumes paused retained sandboxes before reuse, and waits up to the provider readiness budget for cold starts.\n\n## Review fixes included\n\n- Send OpenSandbox execd timeouts in milliseconds.\n- Preserve explicit bash command wrappers and shell-metachar commands.\n- Preserve raw JSON-looking stdout/stderr stream lines.\n- Support bare execd endpoint host:port values with the configured API scheme.\n- Validate Linux-only OpenSandbox platform selection.\n- Verify retained sandbox ownership before reclaiming local leases.\n- Keep created sandboxes reachable with the SDK default entrypoint.\n- Require explicit trusted API endpoints for authenticated calls.\n- Resume paused retained sandboxes before reuse.\n- Use POSIX `sh` for workspace helper commands.\n- Extend sandbox readiness waits beyond the SDK's 30 second default and document the explicit API URL requirement.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test -race -count=1 -run 'TestSDKClientReadyTimeoutUsesProviderBudget|TestSDKClientCreateWaitsForRunningAndExecdPing|TestSDKClientCreateDeletesSandboxWhenReadinessFails|TestNewOpenSandboxClientRequiresExplicitAPIURL' ./internal/providers/opensandbox/`\n- `go test -race -count=1 -run 'TestConfig|Test.*OpenSandbox' ./internal/cli/`\n- `go test -race -count=1 ./internal/providers/opensandbox/`\n- `go test -race -count=1 ./...`\n- Droid/gpt-5.4 autoreview passes were run iteratively; accepted findings through the latest completed pass were fixed and committed. The final rerun was intentionally interrupted when publishing was requested.\n",
